Sentencas: Anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells with diameters of 4 mm based on yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolytes were fabricated by slip-phase inversion combined with a vacuum-assisted coating technique.
Titulo: Tubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by slip-phase inversion combined with a vacuum-assisted coating technique

Sentencas: NiO-YSZ anode tubes were prepared by slip-phase inversion and the YSZ electrolyte membranes were prepared on the NiO-YSZ anodes by the vacuum-assisted coating method.
Titulo: Tubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by slip-phase inversion combined with a vacuum-assisted coating technique

Sentencas: The effect of pre-sintering treatment of anodes on the densification of the supported electrolytes was studied.
Titulo: Tubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by slip-phase inversion combined with a vacuum-assisted coating technique

Sentencas: Dense electrolyte membranes were obtained based on the anodes which were pre-sintered at 1000 degrees C with the co-sintering temperature of 1400 degrees C. Furthermore, an anode functional layer between anode and electrolyte was also fabricated by the vacuum-assisted coating method to enhance the performance of the cell.
Titulo: Tubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by slip-phase inversion combined with a vacuum-assisted coating technique

Sentencas: With La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-0 -YSZ (LSM-YSZ) as the composite cathode, a maximum power density of 178 mW cm(-2) was obtained at 700 degrees C for the single cell with an anode functional layer and a 22-mu m-thick YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Tubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by slip-phase inversion combined with a vacuum-assisted coating technique

Sentencas: Resistances of the tested cells were investigated under open circuit conditions at different operating temperatures by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Tubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by slip-phase inversion combined with a vacuum-assisted coating technique
